@AGENTS.md

## Claude Code specifics

The contract above (from `AGENTS.md`) is authoritative. A few Claude-only notes:

- **The hard invariants are also enforced by hooks**, wired directly into
  `.claude/settings.json` If an `Edit`/`Write` is blocked with a `decanter-guard`
  reason, the edit violated a hard rule — fix the edit, don't try to route around the
  guard.
- **After editing any node source (`.ts`/`.js`) or `n8n-globals.d.ts`**, a PostToolUse
  hook runs `npm run typecheck` and feeds any failure back to you. Treat a failure as a
  blocker to finishing the task.
- **Renames must be atomic** (all four steps in the AGENTS.md rename checklist land in
  one change). Use plan mode for multi-node renames so nothing is left half-updated.
- **`push --force` is blocked from the agent by design.** It overrides the drift guard;
  if it is genuinely needed, ask the user to run it themselves in the terminal.
